1 olive oil
1 carrot
1 beetroot
1 Brown Onion
1 tbs balsamic vinegar
1 tsp brown sugar
1 packet ciabatta
1 packet chicken breast
1 packet garlic aioli
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 bag Mixed Leaves
½ tbs water (for the onion)
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend
½ tbs water (for the dressing)
2 clove garlic

Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced. Cut
carrot into thick half-moons. Cut beetroot into
small chunks. Place veggies on a lined oven tray.
Drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and
pepper. Toss to coat, spread out evenly, then roast
until tender, 25-30 minutes.

While the veggies are roasting, thinly slice onion.
In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil
over medium-high heat. Cook onion, stirring, until
softened, 5-6 minutes. Reduce heat to medium,
then add the balsamic vinegar, water (for the
onion) and the brown sugar. Mix well and cook
until dark and sticky, 3-5 minutes. Transfer to a
bowl.

Little cooks: Don your goggles and have a go at
peeling off the onion's outer layer!

While the onion is cooking, finely chop garlic.
Cut or tear ciabatta into bite-sized chunks. Add
ciabatta and garlic to a second lined oven tray.
Drizzle with olive oil, toss to coat, then sprinkle
over 1/2 the grated Parmesan cheese. Bake until
golden, 5-8 minutes.

Little cooks: Kids can add the finishing touch by
sprinkling the cheese on top.

While the croutons are baking, place your hand
flat on top of each chicken breast and slice
through horizontally to make two thin steaks.
In a large bowl, combine roast chicken sprinkle
and a drizzle of olive oil. Add chicken and turn to
coat. Wash and dry the frying pan, then return to
medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
Cook chicken until cooked through, 3-5 minutes
each side (depending on thickness). Transfer to a
plate to rest.

TIP: The chicken is cooked through when it's no
longer pink inside.

In a small bowl, combine garlic aioli and water
(for the dressing). Set aside. In a large bowl,
combine the white wine vinegar and a drizzle of
olive oil, then season. Add mixed leaves, roasted
veggies and garlic croutons. Gently toss to
combine.

Little cooks: Take the lead by combining the
ingredients for the dressing!

Slice golden chicken. Divide garlic crouton salad
between plates. Top with chicken and caramelised
onion, then pour over any resting juices. Sprinkle
over remaining Parmesan cheese. Drizzle with aioli
dressing to serve.